== Other Places to find Swank ==
<p> Swank has recently been spotted all around the world wide web, and even spraypainted on construction signs. </p>
<p>If you're familiar with the popular website "Nation Sates", there is a reigon, the Swankdom of Superiority, wherein Ommert himself, along with Dan Carmen and others, have settled their respective nations. Wikipedia is the newest website to play host to the word swank, and hopes to further it's spread across the nation. </p>
<p> Somebody, apprarently taking a liking to the word, created a stencil and spraypainted SWANK in orange on a construction sign, located at the top of the hill on Rockland Avenue (located in the Beechview area of Pittsburgh, PA.). The sign has since been removed. Ommert was recently asked to comment. "Personally, I love it. I love anything that furthers our cause. I'd like to stay within the lines of legality, but I must support anything that gets swank out there and in the public eye. I'd like to have a more permanent display than a road sign that isn't even cemented to the ground, but I love it nonetheless." When asked if he was supporting vandalism with this statement, Ommert declined to comment. </p>